com.camerontec.catalys.core.marketstate

Class FixMarketMirror

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.util.configuration.registry.Registerable
      • com.camerontec.catalys.core.marketstate.FixMarketMirror
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IMarketMirror, IConfigurable, IRegisterable, IService

    public class FixMarketMirror
extends Registerable
implements IMarketMirror, IConfigurable
    Implementation of IMarketMirror which maintains the state of a market by processing FIX messages to and from that market.

    This implementation assumes that for each FIX message type tracked by the mirror there is at least one unique or "default" key/tag, for example ClOrdId for orders, ExecId for fills etc. For each type of message (data type) we keep a map indexed by key/tag (at least one) pointing to another map of messages keyed by key/tag values.

    Note: FixMarketMirror is not thread-safe. Client-side synchronization is required if instances of this class are accessed by multiple threads.

      • getExecTypeForDespatch

        public static String getExecTypeForDespatch(IFIXMessage execRpt)
                                     throws ConversionException
        Get the ExecType of an execution report that we can despatch on.

        This is normally just retrieved from the execution report, however, if it is missing (e.g. FIX 4.0) then in most cases we can safely substitute OrdStatus, which should be present.

        The exceptional FIX 4.0 cases we need to handle is when OrdStatus is PartiallyFilled or Filled, but the execution report is not really a fill. This can be the case when OrdStatus priorities are taken into account. That is, semantically this could really be another type of execution report with a lower priority OrdStatus.

        We detect these cases by looking at LastShares. If this is not present, or is 0.0 (or equivalent), then this can't really be a partial fill. That is, OrdStatus is latched due to the previous state of the order. We therefore assume this execution report really represents a Replaced execution. This assumption is safe because the values of OrdStatus that have lower priority then partially filled and filled respectively are not applicable in either case.

        Above is valid when execTransType is New. In case when execTransType is Cancel or Correct we set execType to PartiallyFiled. This is value execType would be in case of FIX4.1 and 4.2. Current order status could be Cancelled.

        Parameters:
        execRpt - The execution report.
        Returns:
        The implied ExecType for the purposes of despatch.
        Throws:
        ConversionException - If the ExecType contained in the execRpt cannot be decoded as a String.

      • configure

        public void configure(IConfiguration configuration)
               throws ConfigurationException
        Description copied from interface: IConfigurable
        Apply the IConfiguration to this IConfigurable.

        This method is called by the configuration module in the server:

        • when loading the configuration at server startup (e.g. when reading the XML configuration file) and
        • every time we reload the configuration object corresponding to the configurable run-time object.
        The Catalys Server passes a reference to a configuration clone. The original reference is unavailable to the configurable object. The configurable object may decide to store the reference as the last valid configuration object which can be used to optimize the re-configuration.
        Specified by:
        configure in interface IConfigurable
        Parameters:
        configuration - the immutable configuration object
        Throws:
        ConfigurationException - This exception is thrown when the new configuration object cannot be applied to the configurable object.
